                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Urgent. The afternoon newspapers report that two American citizens, Charles
                    Barnett and William Leavitt, captured on land, forming part of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Competitor</hi> expedition, are to be tried by ordinary
                    court-martial of the marine jurisdiction. I beg that immediate instruction be
                    given to our legation, Madrid, to ask suspension of the effects of the trial
                    until our Government can be satisfied it is in conformity with the treaty, for I
                    apprehend the condition of the treaty will not be observed.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
